In the older version, the check was:
```c
if (msg_io->scheme == NULL || msg_io->authority == NULL || msg_io->path == NULL)
    return NGHTTP2_ERR_TEMPORAL_CALLBACK_FAILURE;
```
In the newer version, it was updated to:
```c
if (msg_io->authority == NULL) {
    io->in_callback--;
    return NGHTTP2_ERR_TEMPORAL_CALLBACK_FAILURE;
}
```
The condition for 'msg_io->scheme' and 'msg_io->path' was removed, and a decrement of 'io->in_callback' was added.

In the older version, the check was:
```c
if (uri == NULL)
    return NGHTTP2_ERR_TEMPORAL_CALLBACK_FAILURE;
```
In the newer version, it was updated to:
```c
if (uri == NULL) {
    io->in_callback--;
    return NGHTTP2_ERR_TEMPORAL_CALLBACK_FAILURE;
}
```
The newer version adds a decrement of 'io->in_callback' before returning the error.

